** ISO 10328 P5 prosthetic pylon -- submission-agnostic linear static FEA
** Aluminum 6061-T6, two principal static load cases:
**   Step 1 = Test Condition I  (toe heel-off),    F = 3360 N along -Z
**   Step 2 = Test Condition II (heel heel-strike), F = 4000 N along -Z
**
** NSETs (populated by wire_bcs.py from meta.json selectors):
**   NFIXED -- distal clamp face (z_min), pinned in the alignment jig.
**   NLOAD  -- proximal interface face (z_max), where the principal force
**             is delivered through the pyramid adapter.
**
** Eall is auto-built by wire_bcs.py from the gmsh C3D* element sets.

*MATERIAL, NAME=AL6061T6
*ELASTIC
68900., 0.33
*DENSITY
2.7e-9
*SOLID SECTION, ELSET=Eall, MATERIAL=AL6061T6

** ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
** Loading reference node + rigid body coupling
** ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
** A single off-mesh reference node (id 999999) is rigidly coupled to all
** NLOAD nodes; the principal compressive test force is applied at this
** reference node so the total load on the structure equals the standard's
** principal force regardless of how many proximal-face nodes the meshing
** stage produced. This keeps the deck submission-agnostic.
*NODE, NSET=NREF
999999, 0.0, 0.0, 1000.0
*RIGID BODY, NSET=NLOAD, REF NODE=999999

** ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
** Boundary conditions: distal clamp fully fixed
** ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*BOUNDARY
NFIXED, 1, 3, 0.

** ===========================================================================
** Step 1 -- Test Condition I (toe), principal static force 3360 N
** ===========================================================================
*STEP
*STATIC
*CLOAD
999999, 3, -3360.
*NODE FILE
U
*EL FILE
S
*NODE PRINT, NSET=NFIXED, TOTALS=ONLY
RF
*EL PRINT, ELSET=Eall
S
*END STEP

** ===========================================================================
** Step 2 -- Test Condition II (heel), principal static force 4000 N
** ===========================================================================
*STEP
*STATIC
*CLOAD, OP=NEW
999999, 3, -4000.
*NODE FILE
U
*EL FILE
S
*NODE PRINT, NSET=NFIXED, TOTALS=ONLY
RF
*EL PRINT, ELSET=Eall
S
*END STEP
